node.text:
On September 14, New Zealand’s Māori Party filed a petition to change the country’s official name to Aotearoa. The petition describes Aotearoa as the name for the country in 'the first and official language,' Te Reo Māori. Aotearoa translates to 'land of the long white cloud.'

'This petition calls on Parliament to change New Zealand to Aotearoa and begin a process, alongside whānau, hapū, and iwi, local government and the New Zealand Geographic Board to identify and officially restore the original Te Reo Māori names for all towns, cities and places right across the country by 2026,' says the petition.

The petition continues, 'It's well past time that Te Reo Māori was restored to its rightful place as the first and official language of this country. We are a Polynesian country — we are Aotearoa.'

Last year, Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern said she supported more people using the name Aotearoa, which has often been used interchangeably with New Zealand. 'Whether or not we change it in law I don't think changes the fact New Zealanders do increasingly refer to Aotearoa, and I think that's a transition that has been welcomed,' she said, via The Guardian.

However, New Zealand's former Deputy Prime Minister Winston Peters called the petition 'left-wing radical bulldust.' 'Changing our country's name and town and city names is just dumb extremism,' he added.

#newzealand #aotearoa #politics #maori

In a post on Medium last week, Sen. Amy Klobuchar (D-MN) spoke on how a mammogram in February 2021 detected that she had Stage 1A breast cancer. 

She revealed that she had undergone a lumpectomy procedure on her right breast at the Mayo Clinic soon after and completed a course of radiation treatment in May.

In a September 13 appearance on CNN, Sen. Klobuchar discussed how she was fortunate that her doctors caught her cancer early but stressed that she had waited a year to have a mammogram because of the pandemic — similar to how many others are delaying doctor's appointments and exams currently.

'A lot of people are waiting; they think thousands of women have undetected breast cancer right now,' Klobuchar said. She encouraged viewers to go for their physicals and routine examinations, saying, 'It saved my life, and it can save many others.'

node.text:
In a recent podcast interview with theSkimm, Dr. Anthony Fauci expressed support for mandating vaccines for any air travelers. 'I would support that,' Dr. Fauci said. 'If you want to get on a plane and travel with other people ... you should be vaccinated.'⁠
⁠
According to a statement acquired by ABC News, the U.S. Travel Association says it supports the notion that people should get vaccinated before flying. But the org maintains 'that there should be no mandatory vaccination requirement for domestic travel,' adding that 'such a policy would have an unfair, negative impact on families with young children who are not yet eligible to get the vaccine.' A federal transportation mask requirement makes masks mandatory through January 2022. ⁠
⁠
At a press briefing on September 10, White House COVID-19 response coordinator Jeff Zients said that in regards to travel, the Biden administration is taking further action against 'noncompliance of masking on airlines' and they're 'not taking any measures off the table.'⁠

node.text:
12,012 foreign front-line workers in France are now citizens, according to a statement by the French Minister Delegate in Charge of Citizenship Marlène Schiappa on September 9, 2021. The workers were granted citizenship as part of a special program during the COVID-19 crisis to expedite the citizenship applications of people who were on the front lines of the pandemic such as health care workers, security or maintenance officers, child care aides, cashiers, and garbage collectors.⁠
⁠
⁠
#france #citizenship #covid19 #frontlineworkers

node.text:
Former first lady Melania Trump declined to use her platform to advocate for peace during the deadly January 6 riot, sources told CNN.⁠
⁠
The sources say that a top Trump aide had reach out to Trump to ask if she was interested in tweeting a message encouraging non-violent and peaceful protests. Trump reportedly replied, ‘No,’ to the request via text. The aide, Stephanie Grisham, who resigned on January 6 amid the deadly riot, is releasing a book on her experience in the Trump administration.⁠
⁠
⁠
#melaniatrump #january6th #trumpadmin #politics

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NowThis Politics on September 14, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, monument and text.

node.text:
The Capitol Police Board voted on Monday to temporarily erect fencing around the Capitol in light of ‘concerning online chatter’ regarding a pro-January 6 rioters demonstration scheduled for September 18, Chief Tom Manger said in a statement. ‘We want to reassure everyone these are temporary measures to ensure everyone’s safety,’ Manger said.⁠
⁠
The Justice for J6 rally, scheduled for Saturday, was organized to call on the Department of Justice to drop charges against the 550+ individuals facing charges related to January 6. Matt Braynard, an organizer, has said that many were ‘non-violent’ protesters who 'reasonably believed they had permission.’ 5 people died as a result of the January 6 riot, and more than 130 officers were injured.⁠
⁠
⁠
